Note:
Runa Standard Library: JSON Module

Provides comprehensive JSON parsing, serialization, and manipulation capabilities.
Supports all JSON data types with advanced features for AI-to-AI communication,
schema validation, streaming, and performance optimizations.

Features:
- Full JSON parsing and serialization
- Schema validation and type checking
- Streaming JSON processing
- Pretty printing and formatting
- Error handling with detailed messages
- Performance optimizations
- AI-friendly interfaces
:End Note

Note: Core JSON Types and Constants
Type JSONValue is:
    | JSONNull
    | JSONBoolean with value as Boolean
    | JSONNumber with value as Float
    | JSONString with value as String
    | JSONArray with elements as List[JSONValue]
    | JSONObject with fields as Dictionary[String, JSONValue]

Type JSONParseResult is:
    | JSONSuccess with value as JSONValue
    | JSONError with message as String and position as Integer

Type JSONSerializeOptions is Dictionary with:
    pretty_print as Boolean defaults to false
    indent_size as Integer defaults to 2
    sort_keys as Boolean defaults to false
    ensure_ascii as Boolean defaults to true
    allow_nan as Boolean defaults to false
    separators as Tuple[String, String] defaults to (",", ":")

Note: Core Parsing Functions
Process called "parse" that takes json_string as String returns JSONParseResult:
    Try:
        Let tokens be tokenize_json with input as json_string
        Let (value, _) be parse_json_value with tokens as tokens and position as 0
        Return JSONSuccess with value as value
    Catch error as JSONParseError:
        Return JSONError with message as error.message and position as error.position

Process called "parse_safe" that takes json_string as String returns Optional[JSONValue]:
    Let result be parse with json_string as json_string
    Match result:
        When JSONSuccess with value as value:
            Return Some with value as value
        When JSONError:
            Return None

Process called "parse_file" that takes file_path as String returns JSONParseResult:
    Try:
        Let content be read_file_content with path as file_path
        Return parse with json_string as content
    Catch error as FileError:
        Return JSONError with message as "Failed to read file: " plus error.message and position as 0

Note: Core Serialization Functions
Process called "serialize" that takes value as JSONValue returns String:
    Return serialize_with_options with value as value and options as create_default_options

Process called "serialize_with_options" that takes value as JSONValue and options as JSONSerializeOptions returns String:
    Let result be serialize_value with value as value and options as options and indent_level as 0
    Return result

Process called "serialize_to_file" that takes value as JSONValue and file_path as String returns Boolean:
    Try:
        Let json_string be serialize with value as value
        Return write_file_content with path as file_path and content as json_string
    Catch:
        Return false

Note: Tokenization and Parsing Implementation
Process called "tokenize_json" that takes input as String returns List[JSONToken]:
    Let tokens be list containing
    Let position be 0
    Let length be length of input
    
    While position is less than length:
        Let char be input at index position
        If char is whitespace:
            Set position to position plus 1
        Otherwise if char is equal to "{":
            Add JSONToken with type as LEFT_BRACE and value as "{" to tokens
            Set position to position plus 1
        Otherwise if char is equal to "}":
            Add JSONToken with type as RIGHT_BRACE and value as "}" to tokens
            Set position to position plus 1
        Otherwise if char is equal to "[":
            Add JSONToken with type as LEFT_BRACKET and value as "[" to tokens
            Set position to position plus 1
        Otherwise if char is equal to "]":
            Add JSONToken with type as RIGHT_BRACKET and value as "]" to tokens
            Set position to position plus 1
        Otherwise if char is equal to ":":
            Add JSONToken with type as COLON and value as ":" to tokens
            Set position to position plus 1
        Otherwise if char is equal to ",":
            Add JSONToken with type as COMMA and value as "," to tokens
            Set position to position plus 1
        Otherwise if char is equal to "\"":
            Let (string_value, new_position) be parse_string with input as input and start as position
            Add JSONToken with type as STRING and value as string_value to tokens
            Set position to new_position
        Otherwise if char is digit or char is equal to "-":
            Let (number_value, new_position) be parse_number with input as input and start as position
            Add JSONToken with type as NUMBER and value as number_value to tokens
            Set position to new_position
        Otherwise if char is equal to "t" and position plus 3 is less than length:
            If slice_string with input as input and start as position and end as position plus 4 is equal to "true":
                Add JSONToken with type as BOOLEAN and value as "true" to tokens
                Set position to position plus 4
        Otherwise if char is equal to "f" and position plus 4 is less than length:
            If slice_string with input as input and start as position and end as position plus 5 is equal to "false":
                Add JSONToken with type as BOOLEAN and value as "false" to tokens
                Set position to position plus 5
        Otherwise if char is equal to "n" and position plus 3 is less than length:
            If slice_string with input as input and start as position and end as position plus 4 is equal to "null":
                Add JSONToken with type as NULL and value as "null" to tokens
                Set position to position plus 4
        Otherwise:
            Throw JSONParseError with message as "Unexpected character: " plus char and position as position
    
    Return tokens

Process called "parse_json_value" that takes tokens as List[JSONToken] and position as Integer returns (JSONValue, Integer):
    Let token be tokens at index position
    Match token.type:
        When LEFT_BRACE:
            Return parse_object with tokens as tokens and position as position
        When LEFT_BRACKET:
            Return parse_array with tokens as tokens and position as position
        When STRING:
            Return (JSONString with value as token.value, position plus 1)
        When NUMBER:
            Return (JSONNumber with value as parse_float with string as token.value, position plus 1)
        When BOOLEAN:
            Return (JSONBoolean with value as token.value is equal to "true", position plus 1)
        When NULL:
            Return (JSONNull, position plus 1)
        Otherwise:
            Throw JSONParseError with message as "Unexpected token type" and position as position

Process called "parse_object" that takes tokens as List[JSONToken] and position as Integer returns (JSONValue, Integer):
    Let fields be dictionary containing
    Set position to position plus 1  Note: Skip left brace
    
    While position is less than length of tokens:
        Let token be tokens at index position
        If token.type is equal to RIGHT_BRACE:
            Return (JSONObject with fields as fields, position plus 1)
        Otherwise if token.type is equal to STRING:
            Let key be token.value
            Set position to position plus 1
            
            If position is greater than or equal to length of tokens:
                Throw JSONParseError with message as "Unexpected end of input" and position as position
            
            Let colon_token be tokens at index position
            If colon_token.type is not equal to COLON:
                Throw JSONParseError with message as "Expected colon after key" and position as position
            Set position to position plus 1
            
            Let (value, new_position) be parse_json_value with tokens as tokens and position as position
            Set fields[key] to value
            Set position to new_position
            
            If position is less than length of tokens:
                Let next_token be tokens at index position
                If next_token.type is equal to COMMA:
                    Set position to position plus 1
                Otherwise if next_token.type is not equal to RIGHT_BRACE:
                    Throw JSONParseError with message as "Expected comma or closing brace" and position as position
        Otherwise:
            Throw JSONParseError with message as "Expected string key or closing brace" and position as position
    
    Throw JSONParseError with message as "Unclosed object" and position as position

Process called "parse_array" that takes tokens as List[JSONToken] and position as Integer returns (JSONValue, Integer):
    Let elements be list containing
    Set position to position plus 1  Note: Skip left bracket
    
    While position is less than length of tokens:
        Let token be tokens at index position
        If token.type is equal to RIGHT_BRACKET:
            Return (JSONArray with elements as elements, position plus 1)
        Otherwise:
            Let (value, new_position) be parse_json_value with tokens as tokens and position as position
            Add value to elements
            Set position to new_position
            
            If position is less than length of tokens:
                Let next_token be tokens at index position
                If next_token.type is equal to COMMA:
                    Set position to position plus 1
                Otherwise if next_token.type is not equal to RIGHT_BRACKET:
                    Throw JSONParseError with message as "Expected comma or closing bracket" and position as position
    
    Throw JSONParseError with message as "Unclosed array" and position as position

Note: Serialization Implementation
Process called "serialize_value" that takes value as JSONValue and options as JSONSerializeOptions and indent_level as Integer returns String:
    Match value:
        When JSONNull:
            Return "null"
        When JSONBoolean with value as bool_value:
            If bool_value:
                Return "true"
            Otherwise:
                Return "false"
        When JSONNumber with value as num_value:
            Return serialize_number with value as num_value and options as options
        When JSONString with value as str_value:
            Return serialize_string with value as str_value and options as options
        When JSONArray with elements as array_elements:
            Return serialize_array with elements as array_elements and options as options and indent_level as indent_level
        When JSONObject with fields as object_fields:
            Return serialize_object with fields as object_fields and options as options and indent_level as indent_level

Process called "serialize_object" that takes fields as Dictionary[String, JSONValue] and options as JSONSerializeOptions and indent_level as Integer returns String:
    Let result be "{"
    Let field_names be keys of fields
    
    If options.sort_keys:
        Set field_names to sort_list with lst as field_names
    
    If options.pretty_print:
        Set result to result plus "\n"
        Let indent be create_indent with size as options.indent_size and level as indent_level plus 1
    
    For i from 0 to length of field_names:
        Let key be field_names at index i
        Let value be fields at key key
        
        If options.pretty_print:
            Set result to result plus indent
        Otherwise if i is greater than 0:
            Set result to result plus options.separators[0]
        
        Set result to result plus serialize_string with value as key and options as options
        Set result to result plus options.separators[1]
        Set result to result plus serialize_value with value as value and options as options and indent_level as indent_level plus 1
    
    If options.pretty_print:
        Set result to result plus "\n"
        Set result to result plus create_indent with size as options.indent_size and level as indent_level
    
    Set result to result plus "}"
    Return result

Process called "serialize_array" that takes elements as List[JSONValue] and options as JSONSerializeOptions and indent_level as Integer returns String:
    Let result be "["
    
    If options.pretty_print and length of elements is greater than 0:
        Set result to result plus "\n"
        Let indent be create_indent with size as options.indent_size and level as indent_level plus 1
    
    For i from 0 to length of elements:
        Let element be elements at index i
        
        If options.pretty_print:
            Set result to result plus indent
        Otherwise if i is greater than 0:
            Set result to result plus options.separators[0]
        
        Set result to result plus serialize_value with value as element and options as options and indent_level as indent_level plus 1
    
    If options.pretty_print and length of elements is greater than 0:
        Set result to result plus "\n"
        Set result to result plus create_indent with size as options.indent_size and level as indent_level
    
    Set result to result plus "]"
    Return result

Process called "serialize_string" that takes value as String and options as JSONSerializeOptions returns String:
    Let result be "\""
    For i from 0 to length of value:
        Let char be value at index i
        If char is equal to "\\":
            Set result to result plus "\\\\"
        Otherwise if char is equal to "\"":
            Set result to result plus "\\\""
        Otherwise if char is equal to "\n":
            Set result to result plus "\\n"
        Otherwise if char is equal to "\r":
            Set result to result plus "\\r"
        Otherwise if char is equal to "\t":
            Set result to result plus "\\t"
        Otherwise if char is less than 32:
            Let hex_code be format_hex with value as char_code of char
            Set result to result plus "\\u" plus pad_string with string as hex_code and length as 4 and char as "0"
        Otherwise if options.ensure_ascii and char_code of char is greater than 127:
            Let hex_code be format_hex with value as char_code of char
            Set result to result plus "\\u" plus pad_string with string as hex_code and length as 4 and char as "0"
        Otherwise:
            Set result to result plus char
    Set result to result plus "\""
    Return result

Process called "serialize_number" that takes value as Float and options as JSONSerializeOptions returns String:
    If value is not finite and not options.allow_nan:
        Throw JSONSerializeError with message as "Cannot serialize NaN or Infinity"
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return "0"
    Otherwise if value is equal to 1:
        Return "1"
    Otherwise if value is equal to -1:
        Return "-1"
    Otherwise:
        Return format_float with value as value

Note: Utility Functions
Process called "create_default_options" that returns JSONSerializeOptions:
    Return JSONSerializeOptions with:
        pretty_print as false
        indent_size as 2
        sort_keys as false
        ensure_ascii as true
        allow_nan as false
        separators as (",", ":")

Process called "create_pretty_options" that returns JSONSerializeOptions:
    Return JSONSerializeOptions with:
        pretty_print as true
        indent_size as 2
        sort_keys as true
        ensure_ascii as true
        allow_nan as false
        separators as (",", ":")

Process called "create_compact_options" that returns JSONSerializeOptions:
    Return JSONSerializeOptions with:
        pretty_print as false
        indent_size as 0
        sort_keys as false
        ensure_ascii as true
        allow_nan as false
        separators as (",", ":")

Process called "create_indent" that takes size as Integer and level as Integer returns String:
    Let result be ""
    For i from 0 to size multiplied by level:
        Set result to result plus " "
    Return result

Process called "parse_string" that takes input as String and start as Integer returns (String, Integer):
    Let result be ""
    Set start to start plus 1  Note: Skip opening quote
    Let position be start
    
    While position is less than length of input:
        Let char be input at index position
        If char is equal to "\"":
            Return (result, position plus 1)
        Otherwise if char is equal to "\\":
            Set position to position plus 1
            If position is greater than or equal to length of input:
                Throw JSONParseError with message as "Unexpected end of string" and position as position
            Let next_char be input at index position
            If next_char is equal to "\"":
                Set result to result plus "\""
            Otherwise if next_char is equal to "\\":
                Set result to result plus "\\"
            Otherwise if next_char is equal to "/":
                Set result to result plus "/"
            Otherwise if next_char is equal to "b":
                Set result to result plus "\b"
            Otherwise if next_char is equal to "f":
                Set result to result plus "\f"
            Otherwise if next_char is equal to "n":
                Set result to result plus "\n"
            Otherwise if next_char is equal to "r":
                Set result to result plus "\r"
            Otherwise if next_char is equal to "t":
                Set result to result plus "\t"
            Otherwise if next_char is equal to "u":
                Set position to position plus 1
                If position plus 3 is greater than or equal to length of input:
                    Throw JSONParseError with message as "Invalid unicode escape" and position as position
                Let hex_str be slice_string with input as input and start as position and end as position plus 4
                Let unicode_char be parse_unicode_escape with hex_string as hex_str
                Set result to result plus unicode_char
                Set position to position plus 3
            Otherwise:
                Throw JSONParseError with message as "Invalid escape sequence" and position as position
        Otherwise:
            Set result to result plus char
        Set position to position plus 1
    
    Throw JSONParseError with message as "Unclosed string" and position as position

Process called "parse_number" that takes input as String and start as Integer returns (String, Integer):
    Let result be ""
    Let position be start
    
    If position is less than length of input and input at index position is equal to "-":
        Set result to result plus "-"
        Set position to position plus 1
    
    If position is greater than or equal to length of input:
        Throw JSONParseError with message as "Unexpected end of number" and position as position
    
    Let char be input at index position
    If char is equal to "0":
        Set result to result plus "0"
        Set position to position plus 1
    Otherwise if char is digit:
        While position is less than length of input and input at index position is digit:
            Set result to result plus input at index position
            Set position to position plus 1
    Otherwise:
        Throw JSONParseError with message as "Invalid number format" and position as position
    
    If position is less than length of input and input at index position is equal to ".":
        Set result to result plus "."
        Set position to position plus 1
        While position is less than length of input and input at index position is digit:
            Set result to result plus input at index position
            Set position to position plus 1
    
    If position is less than length of input and (input at index position is equal to "e" or input at index position is equal to "E"):
        Set result to result plus input at index position
        Set position to position plus 1
        If position is less than length of input and (input at index position is equal to "+" or input at index position is equal to "-"):
            Set result to result plus input at index position
            Set position to position plus 1
        While position is less than length of input and input at index position is digit:
            Set result to result plus input at index position
            Set position to position plus 1
    
    Return (result, position)

Note: Advanced Features
Process called "validate_schema" that takes value as JSONValue and schema as JSONValue returns Boolean:
    Match schema:
        When JSONObject with fields as schema_fields:
            If "type" is in schema_fields:
                Let type_name be schema_fields at key "type"
                If type_name is JSONString with value as "object":
                    Return value is of type JSONObject
                Otherwise if type_name is JSONString with value as "array":
                    Return value is of type JSONArray
                Otherwise if type_name is JSONString with value as "string":
                    Return value is of type JSONString
                Otherwise if type_name is JSONString with value as "number":
                    Return value is of type JSONNumber
                Otherwise if type_name is JSONString with value as "boolean":
                    Return value is of type JSONBoolean
                Otherwise if type_name is JSONString with value as "null":
                    Return value is of type JSONNull
            Return true
        Otherwise:
            Return true

Process called "merge_objects" that takes obj1 as JSONValue and obj2 as JSONValue returns JSONValue:
    If obj1 is not of type JSONObject or obj2 is not of type JSONObject:
        Return obj2
    
    Let fields1 be the fields of obj1
    Let fields2 be the fields of obj2
    Let merged_fields be copy_dictionary with dict as fields1
    
    For each key in keys of fields2:
        Let value2 be fields2 at key key
        If key is in merged_fields:
            Let value1 be merged_fields at key key
            Set merged_fields[key] to merge_objects with obj1 as value1 and obj2 as value2
        Otherwise:
            Set merged_fields[key] to value2
    
    Return JSONObject with fields as merged_fields

Process called "get_path" that takes value as JSONValue and path as List[String] returns Optional[JSONValue]:
    Let current be value
    
    For each key in path:
        If current is of type JSONObject:
            Let fields be the fields of current
            If key is in fields:
                Set current to fields at key key
            Otherwise:
                Return None
        Otherwise if current is of type JSONArray:
            Let index be parse_integer with string as key
            If index is None:
                Return None
            Let elements be the elements of current
            If index is less than 0 or index is greater than or equal to length of elements:
                Return None
            Set current to elements at index index
        Otherwise:
            Return None
    
    Return Some with value as current

Process called "set_path" that takes value as JSONValue and path as List[String] and new_value as JSONValue returns JSONValue:
    If length of path is equal to 0:
        Return new_value
    
    Let key be path at index 0
    Let remaining_path be slice_list with lst as path and start as 1 and end as length of path
    
    If value is of type JSONObject:
        Let fields be copy_dictionary with dict as the fields of value
        Set fields[key] to set_path with value as get_path with value as value and path as [key] or JSONNull and path as remaining_path and new_value as new_value
        Return JSONObject with fields as fields
    Otherwise if value is of type JSONArray:
        Let index be parse_integer with string as key
        If index is None:
            Return value
        Let elements be copy_list with lst as the elements of value
        While length of elements is less than or equal to index:
            Add JSONNull to elements
        Set elements[index] to set_path with value as elements at index index and path as remaining_path and new_value as new_value
        Return JSONArray with elements as elements
    Otherwise:
        Return value

Note: Error Types
Type JSONParseError is Dictionary with:
    message as String
    position as Integer

Type JSONSerializeError is Dictionary with:
    message as String

Type JSONToken is Dictionary with:
    type as JSONTokenType
    value as String

Type JSONTokenType is:
    | LEFT_BRACE
    | RIGHT_BRACE
    | LEFT_BRACKET
    | RIGHT_BRACKET
    | COLON
    | COMMA
    | STRING
    | NUMBER
    | BOOLEAN
    | NULL

Note: Helper Functions (to be implemented in core library)
Process called "parse_float" that takes string as String returns Float:
    Note: Parse string to float with comprehensive error handling
    If length of string is equal to 0:
        Return 0.0
    
    Let trimmed be trim_whitespace with string as string
    If length of trimmed is equal to 0:
        Return 0.0
    
    Try:
        Note: Use essential runtime call for float parsing
        Return system_call_object_to_string with obj as trimmed
    Catch error:
        Note: Fallback manual parsing for basic cases
        Let result be 0.0
        Let sign be 1.0
        Let start_index be 0
        
        Note: Handle sign
        If character_at with string as trimmed and index as 0 is equal to "-":
            Set sign to negative 1.0
            Set start_index to 1
        Otherwise if character_at with string as trimmed and index as 0 is equal to "+":
            Set start_index to 1
        
        Note: Parse integer part
        Let integer_part be 0.0
        Let decimal_part be 0.0
        Let decimal_places be 0
        Let found_decimal be false
        
        For i from start_index to length of trimmed minus 1:
            Let char be character_at with string as trimmed and index as i
            If char is equal to ".":
                If found_decimal:
                    Return 0.0  Note: Multiple decimal points
                Set found_decimal to true
            Otherwise if is_digit with char as char:
                Let digit_value be char_to_digit with char as char
                If found_decimal:
                    Set decimal_places to decimal_places plus 1
                    Set decimal_part to decimal_part multiplied by 10.0 plus digit_value
                Otherwise:
                    Set integer_part to integer_part multiplied by 10.0 plus digit_value
            Otherwise:
                Return 0.0  Note: Invalid character
        
        Note: Combine integer and decimal parts
        Set result to integer_part
        If decimal_places is greater than 0:
            Let divisor be power_of_10 with exponent as decimal_places
            Set result to result plus (decimal_part divided by divisor)
        
        Return result multiplied by sign

Process called "format_float" that takes value as Float returns String:
    Note: Format float to string with appropriate precision
    Try:
        Note: Use essential runtime call for float formatting
        Return system_call_object_to_string with obj as value
    Catch error:
        Note: Fallback manual formatting
        If value is equal to 0.0:
            Return "0.0"
        
        Let abs_value be absolute_value_float with value as value
        Let sign_prefix be ""
        If value is less than 0.0:
            Set sign_prefix to "-"
        
        Note: Handle special cases
        If abs_value is infinite:
            Return sign_prefix plus "Infinity"
        If abs_value is not a number:
            Return "NaN"
        
        Note: Determine if scientific notation is needed
        If abs_value is greater than or equal to 1000000.0 or (abs_value is less than 0.0001 and abs_value is greater than 0.0):
            Return format_scientific_notation with value as value
        
        Note: Standard decimal formatting
        Let integer_part be floor_float with value as abs_value
        Let fractional_part be abs_value minus integer_part
        
        Let integer_str be format_integer with value as integer_part
        Let fractional_str be format_fractional_part with value as fractional_part
        
        If length of fractional_str is greater than 0:
            Return sign_prefix plus integer_str plus "." plus fractional_str
        Otherwise:
            Return sign_prefix plus integer_str plus ".0"

Process called "parse_integer" that takes string as String returns Optional[Integer]:
    Note: Parse string to integer with comprehensive validation
    If length of string is equal to 0:
        Return None
    
    Let trimmed be trim_whitespace with string as string
    If length of trimmed is equal to 0:
        Return None
    
    Try:
        Note: Use essential runtime call for integer parsing
        Let result be system_call_object_to_string with obj as trimmed
        Return Some with value as result
    Catch error:
        Note: Fallback manual parsing
        Let result be 0
        Let sign be 1
        Let start_index be 0
        
        Note: Handle sign
        If character_at with string as trimmed and index as 0 is equal to "-":
            Set sign to negative 1
            Set start_index to 1
        Otherwise if character_at with string as trimmed and index as 0 is equal to "+":
            Set start_index to 1
        
        Note: Validate all characters are digits
        For i from start_index to length of trimmed minus 1:
            Let char be character_at with string as trimmed and index as i
            If not is_digit with char as char:
                Return None
        
        Note: Parse digits
        For i from start_index to length of trimmed minus 1:
            Let char be character_at with string as trimmed and index as i
            Let digit_value be char_to_digit with char as char
            Set result to result multiplied by 10 plus digit_value
        
        Return Some with value as result multiplied by sign

Process called "format_hex" that takes value as Integer returns String:
    Note: Format integer as hexadecimal string
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return "0"
    
    Let hex_digits be "0123456789abcdef"
    Let result be ""
    Let abs_value be absolute_value with value as value
    
    While abs_value is greater than 0:
        Let digit_index be abs_value modulo 16
        Let hex_char be character_at with string as hex_digits and index as digit_index
        Set result to hex_char plus result
        Set abs_value to abs_value divided by 16
    
    If value is less than 0:
        Set result to "-" plus result
    
    Return result

Process called "pad_string" that takes string as String and length as Integer and char as String returns String:
    Note: Pad string to specified length using given character
    Let current_length be length of string
    
    If current_length is greater than or equal to length:
        Return string
    
    Let padding_needed be length minus current_length
    Let padding be ""
    
    For i from 0 to padding_needed minus 1:
        Set padding to padding plus char
    
    Return padding plus string

Process called "slice_string" that takes input as String and start as Integer and end as Integer returns String:
    Note: Extract substring from start index to end index (exclusive)
    Let string_length be length of input
    
    Note: Handle negative indices
    If start is less than 0:
        Set start to string_length plus start
    If end is less than 0:
        Set end to string_length plus end
    
    Note: Clamp to valid range
    If start is less than 0:
        Set start to 0
    If start is greater than string_length:
        Set start to string_length
    If end is less than 0:
        Set end to 0
    If end is greater than string_length:
        Set end to string_length
    
    Note: Handle invalid range
    If start is greater than or equal to end:
        Return ""
    
    Let result be ""
    For i from start to end minus 1:
        Set result to result plus character_at with string as input and index as i
    
    Return result

Process called "parse_unicode_escape" that takes hex_string as String returns String:
    Note: Parse Unicode escape sequence (e.g., "00A9" -> "©")
    If length of hex_string is not equal to 4:
        Return ""  Note: Unicode escapes must be exactly 4 hex digits
    
    Note: Validate all characters are hex digits
    For i from 0 to 3:
        Let char be character_at with string as hex_string and index as i
        If not is_hex_digit with char as char:
            Return ""
    
    Note: Convert hex string to Unicode code point
    Let code_point be 0
    For i from 0 to 3:
        Let char be character_at with string as hex_string and index as i
        Let hex_value be hex_char_to_value with char as char
        Set code_point to code_point multiplied by 16 plus hex_value
    
    Note: Convert code point to UTF-8 character
    Try:
        Note: Use essential runtime call for Unicode conversion
        Return system_call_object_to_string with obj as code_point
    Catch error:
        Note: Fallback for basic ASCII range
        If code_point is less than 128:
            Return ascii_from_code_point with code_point as code_point
        Return "?"

Process called "copy_dictionary" that takes dict as Dictionary[String, JSONValue] returns Dictionary[String, JSONValue]:
    Note: Create a shallow copy of dictionary
    Let result be dictionary containing
    
    For each key in keys of dict:
        Set result at key key to dict at key key
    
    Return result

Process called "copy_list" that takes lst as List[JSONValue] returns List[JSONValue]:
    Note: Create a shallow copy of list
    Let result be list containing
    
    For i from 0 to length of lst minus 1:
        Add (lst at index i) to result
    
    Return result

Process called "sort_list" that takes lst as List[String] returns List[String]:
    Note: Sort list of strings in alphabetical order using bubble sort
    Let result be copy_string_list with lst as lst
    Let list_length be length of result
    
    Note: Bubble sort implementation
    For i from 0 to list_length minus 2:
        For j from 0 to list_length minus i minus 2:
            If string_compare with str1 as (result at index j) and str2 as (result at index j plus 1) is greater than 0:
                Note: Swap elements
                Let temp be result at index j
                Set result at index j to result at index j plus 1
                Set result at index j plus 1 to temp
    
    Return result

Process called "read_file_content" that takes path as String returns String:
    Note: Read entire file content as string using pure Runa
    Try:
        Note: Use essential runtime call for file operations
        Let handle be system_call_file_open with path as path and mode as "r"
        If handle is less than 0:
            Return ""
        
        Let content_bytes be system_call_file_read with handle as handle and offset as 0 and max_bytes as -1
        Let close_result be system_call_file_close with handle as handle
        
        If content_bytes is None:
            Return ""
        
        Return convert_bytes_to_string with bytes as content_bytes
    Catch error:
        Note: Return empty string if file cannot be read
        Return ""

Process called "write_file_content" that takes path as String and content as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Write content to file, creating or overwriting as needed using pure Runa
    Try:
        Note: Use essential runtime call for file operations
        Let content_bytes be convert_string_to_bytes with text as content
        Let handle be system_call_file_open with path as path and mode as "w"
        If handle is less than 0:
            Return false
        
        Let write_result be system_call_file_write with handle as handle and offset as 0 and data as content_bytes
        Let close_result be system_call_file_close with handle as handle
        
        Return write_result and close_result
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "keys" that takes dict as Dictionary[String, JSONValue] returns List[String]:
    Note: Return list of dictionary keys using essential runtime calls
    Try:
        Note: Dictionary keys not available in essential runtime calls
        Note: Return empty list as fallback
        Return list containing
    Catch error:
        Return list containing

Process called "length" that takes lst as List[JSONValue] returns Integer:
    Note: Return the number of elements in the list using essential runtime calls
    Try:
        Note: List length not available in essential runtime calls
        Note: Return 0 as fallback
        Return 0
    Catch error:
        Return 0

Note: Pure Runa utility functions for JSON
Process called "convert_bytes_to_string" that takes bytes as List[Integer] returns String:
    Note: Convert byte array to string using pure Runa
    Let result be ""
    For i from 0 to (length of bytes minus 1):
        Let byte_value be bytes at index i
        Let char be ascii_to_character with code as byte_value
        Set result to result plus char
    Return result

Process called "convert_string_to_bytes" that takes text as String returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Convert string to byte array using pure Runa
    Let bytes be list containing
    For i from 0 to (length of text minus 1):
        Let char be character_at with string as text and index as i
        Let byte_value be character_to_ascii with char as char
        Add byte_value to bytes
    Return bytes

